<subSubSection id="23785C44285F0C3132BA03F939A5877A" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="3F10A39E411CB1C2A7434F694F4D1CB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B54407023C38EF978C4526E1442C4CF0" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="06F0E7DE6503E82435B791CCAFB2DA42" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<typeStatus id="72F69620D61B88E8B0F91F0AF6F04D60">Holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
, NIGP179427, female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B850A8B5F1872C92499C32150C065905" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="30393675B9FEF5494A5D6F71B26FE0E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BCDF67587869C144781BE6C426CC815D" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">The specific name refers to its distinctly serrate antennae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20DBBAA8246876D3B0F75724F69D8A60" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="locality and horizon">
<paragraph id="CA21ADFADD75E4340A1C78D98730246A" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Locality and horizon.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FFB29B8029D5B95B8C6D88CF9270B3D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Amber mine located near Noije Bum Village (
<geoCoordinate id="BAEBCD04C3105ECCF2FC35344920014A" degrees="26" direction="north" minutes="20" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="26.333334">26°20'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="FC7F6CF6BF6B9BCC8DC50FAC8B03E7A1" degrees="96" direction="east" minutes="36" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="96.6">96°36'E</geoCoordinate>
), Tanai Township, Myitkyina District, Kachin State, Myanmar; unnamed horizon, mid-Cretaceous, Upper Albian to Lower Cenomanian.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2BECB2622C7BB34B81C1AF9C1F7ECF64" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5FB94128FBFC082950F4822B413A6785" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="483A11F7434C02F75138DBB0B389BA38" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">As for the genus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="38315F3D6AD5AC8185D83528FF2B0DE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="7EA927A0A538544AAA2DD99095F758AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E49AED916E645D4C5D2CD20DBF8F645C" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B31269F3B730C512C2A662C28F48F76F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Adult female.</emphasis>
Body weakly sclerotized, elongate, about 5.3 mm long, 1.4 mm wide (widest across abdomen).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9A7A150B65AF889F8489BC9C86349C3B" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="7120DD3AD1D538F04FC900B83776728F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A2E6F6F913D8CDF3BC1EBAFBE8556356" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A head, ventral view, showing the confluent gular suture (arrowhead) B prothorax, ventral view C metathorax, ventral view D abdominal base, ventral view E abdominal apex, ventral view F head, dorsal view G prothorax, dorsal view H elytral base, dorsal view H abdominal apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; v 1 - 7, ventrites 1 - 7. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667939" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">3A,F</figureCitation>
) fully exposed, prognathous, subquadrate, weakly narrowed posteriorly, including eyes almost as wide as pronotum; dorsal surface flat, without protuberance or depression. Compound eyes moderately large and weakly protruding, finely facetted, without interfacetal setae. Antennal insertions located anteriorly, dorsally exposed, separated by approximately the length of antennomere 1. Subantennal grooves absent. Antennae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E41D500DFB8C66E7FEE0FA966A7C49A5" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A mouthparts, ventral view B antennal base, dorsal view C antennal apex D mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) E abdominal apex, dorsal view F ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst 1 - 5, mesotarsomeres 1 - 5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">4B,C</figureCitation>
) with 11 antennomeres; antennomere 1 moderately broad; antennomeres 2 short; antennomere 3-10 distinctly serrate. Mandibles with one prominent tooth on incisor edge (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5D0DA974D618E2CEB8ADE99F38DAD61C" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427 A dorsal view B ventral view C lateral view D anterodorsal view E anterolateral view. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667941" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">5D</figureCitation>
). Apical maxillary and labial palpomeres elongate, symmetrical, fusiform, not unequally expanded, apex acute (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2DAB661A423B99B6F7AEC2AECAC84F87" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A mouthparts, ventral view B antennal base, dorsal view C antennal apex D mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) E abdominal apex, dorsal view F ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst 1 - 5, mesotarsomeres 1 - 5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">4A</figureCitation>
). Gular sutures confluent (Figs 
<figureCitation id="4D8FA038966C5FB785E3C4F1265F48F2" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A head, ventral view, showing the confluent gular suture (arrowhead) B prothorax, ventral view C metathorax, ventral view D abdominal base, ventral view E abdominal apex, ventral view F head, dorsal view G prothorax, dorsal view H elytral base, dorsal view H abdominal apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; v 1 - 7, ventrites 1 - 7. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667939" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FD05E5AD27B414BC45431772A267151B" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427 A dorsal view B ventral view C lateral view D anterodorsal view E anterolateral view. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667941" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="9EAF9C6B2F9935B34526BCCBBD7B343D" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="9A11F6AE6E2032EA91598B7650DBF437" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="3AC5F1AF693031CE45685724EF069E0F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Figure 4.</emphasis>
Details of 
<taxonomicName id="1EEA8518532BCFC0278EFAE45F7879BD" authorityName="Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Nothotytthonyx" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nothotytthonyx serratus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis id="117703A1E624FC9E98A657BA0509B42B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Nothotytthonyx serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179427, under confocal microscopy 
<emphasis id="F30B1658BE1A1EEE612BB7B1B35215DC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">A</emphasis>
mouthparts, ventral view 
<emphasis id="47B3ED62CD63B4451A2825D9125E8CA4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B</emphasis>
antennal base, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="ACA3B2205AB62A677EA9312884FF5C24" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">C</emphasis>
antennal apex 
<emphasis id="508163A8BAA9A76F22A7E0DA2CC8A0AF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">D</emphasis>
mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) 
<emphasis id="7EA4D07359A093ACB9BCB7EA5E3BFE92" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">E</emphasis>
abdominal apex, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="4118646EF2A867E6FDF5E06106514222" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">F</emphasis>
ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an1-11, antennomeres 1-11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst1-5, mesotarsomeres 1-5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 
<normalizedToken id="A9CE95F916682110E292A4FD4D1EDCCF" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="641A4EDF0BA9F3D3BEAA19F19A89F356" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1C6F7D1C560FD016B67785E9D90A4262" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A head, ventral view, showing the confluent gular suture (arrowhead) B prothorax, ventral view C metathorax, ventral view D abdominal base, ventral view E abdominal apex, ventral view F head, dorsal view G prothorax, dorsal view H elytral base, dorsal view H abdominal apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; v 1 - 7, ventrites 1 - 7. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667939" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">3G</figureCitation>
) transverse; anterior and posterior angles broadly rounded; lateral and posterior margins clearly bordered. Elytra (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="876DD331AA141540D09FDAD9E9EA3CEF" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A head, ventral view, showing the confluent gular suture (arrowhead) B prothorax, ventral view C metathorax, ventral view D abdominal base, ventral view E abdominal apex, ventral view F head, dorsal view G prothorax, dorsal view H elytral base, dorsal view H abdominal apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; v 1 - 7, ventrites 1 - 7. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667939" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">3H</figureCitation>
) relatively short, covering only about half of posterior body; surface somewhat punctate. Procoxae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9892400312585F907794C274E59ACDC9" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427 A dorsal view B ventral view C lateral view D anterodorsal view E anterolateral view. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667941" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">5B</figureCitation>
) conical, well projecting, contiguous. Mesocoxae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CDFDC687C4739D7F5F5524816009A333" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427 A dorsal view B ventral view C lateral view D anterodorsal view E anterolateral view. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667941" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">5B</figureCitation>
) conical, well projecting, narrowly separated. Metaventrite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="322D5A10F29D2551FFE7E9EF5B06BA3C" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A head, ventral view, showing the confluent gular suture (arrowhead) B prothorax, ventral view C metathorax, ventral view D abdominal base, ventral view E abdominal apex, ventral view F head, dorsal view G prothorax, dorsal view H elytral base, dorsal view H abdominal apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; v 1 - 7, ventrites 1 - 7. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667939" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">3C</figureCitation>
) large, with distinct discrimen and metakatepisternal suture. Metacoxae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C6D377E519B414359D185364EDE1F7B4" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A head, ventral view, showing the confluent gular suture (arrowhead) B prothorax, ventral view C metathorax, ventral view D abdominal base, ventral view E abdominal apex, ventral view F head, dorsal view G prothorax, dorsal view H elytral base, dorsal view H abdominal apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; md, mandible; msf, mesofemur; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; v 1 - 7, ventrites 1 - 7. Scale bars: 300 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667939" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">3C</figureCitation>
) transverse, almost contiguous.
</paragraph>
<caption id="E9674F4D1164D842D21397BECAD08692" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667941" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph id="71A3BC81CE1E07AC4A4B56CA036EE9AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="EEC4E3A3E97D1AD9CAB576E3DABF816C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Figure 5.</emphasis>
X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of 
<taxonomicName id="E00D838E5FB4F724DBE51AAAF458F780" authorityName="Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Nothotytthonyx" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nothotytthonyx serratus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis id="517B3A634A25D3FF69FC6474922794A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Nothotytthonyx serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP179427 
<emphasis id="11424479E00110BBB550F18C496EB86E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">A</emphasis>
dorsal view 
<emphasis id="E70D73CC8BB4CB65AD87CEC1A3A35AC1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">B</emphasis>
ventral view 
<emphasis id="8BA7C5919CCBBDFE21473FCD6FF2B2B5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">C</emphasis>
lateral view 
<emphasis id="F29C5E4B275B1F1E304488FDDD76C516" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">D</emphasis>
anterodorsal view 
<emphasis id="C4319A5BDB5EADF3E4E0C054E844DF79" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">E</emphasis>
anterolateral view. Scale bar: 2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="9D97298AC15F2D5F498D98EE65C88BD0" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="F5913CD40AD0DBFA11BEEA9706709ECD" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Legs</emphasis>
slender. Trochanters obliquely articulated to femoral bases. Tibiae with weak spurs (at least as seen on left mesotibia; Fig. 
<figureCitation id="007D6819FD59EE5F4FDBEB3099370FDD" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A mouthparts, ventral view B antennal base, dorsal view C antennal apex D mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) E abdominal apex, dorsal view F ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst 1 - 5, mesotarsomeres 1 - 5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">4D</figureCitation>
). Tarsal formula 5-5-5; tarsomere 4 ventrally bilobed (Figs 
<figureCitation id="F78DC874E7687F8A2665771A87D16417" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A mouthparts, ventral view B antennal base, dorsal view C antennal apex D mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) E abdominal apex, dorsal view F ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst 1 - 5, mesotarsomeres 1 - 5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">4D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="7F1B93A5D72F0098AF79EF2082CD88D7" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. X-ray microtomographic reconstruction of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427 A dorsal view B ventral view C lateral view D anterodorsal view E anterolateral view. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667941" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">5E</figureCitation>
). Claws simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="733E04A1E80DC6739A979BB1AB26CCD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="BD7AF00DBAA0B4A51D6B04D22E01243D" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Abdomen</emphasis>
with seven free ventrites. Gonostyli well developed (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="041B4E41E65F9C92B6AD8BE7E4DB849C" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Nothotytthonyx serratus Li, Biffi, Kundrata &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP 179427, under confocal microscopy A mouthparts, ventral view B antennal base, dorsal view C antennal apex D mid leg, showing the two weak tibial spurs (arrowhead) E abdominal apex, dorsal view F ovipositor, ventral view. Abbreviations: an 1 - 11, antennomeres 1 - 11; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; lbp, labial palp; mst 1 - 5, mesotarsomeres 1 - 5; mstb, mesotibia; mxp, maxillary palp. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.81701.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667940" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
